{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_15063fdb84c041e79c76db26","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Feature: Fix Chat Issues and Integrate Memory System\n2\t\n3\t## Overview\n4\t\n5\tFix critical chat issues and integrate with the Memory system to provide a complete chat experience with persistent history and knowledge sharing.\n6\t\n7\t## Requirements\n8\t\n9\t### 1. Chat Message Delivery Fix\n10\t**Current Issue**: When user sends a message in chat, there is no AI response.\n11\t\n12\t**Expected Behavior**:\n13\t- User message is sent to LLM API\n14\t- AI response is received and displayed\n15\t- No blocking or hanging on send\n16\t\n17\t### 2. Chat History Persistence\n18\t**Current Issue**: When switching tabs and returning to chat, the conversation history is lost.\n19\t\n20\t**Expected Behavior**:\n21\t- Chat history is saved to IndexedDB/Database\n22\t- History persists across tab switches\n23\t- History persists across page reloads\n24\t- Load from DB when chat component mounts\n25\t\n26\t### 3. Memory System Integration\n27\t**Current Issue**: Chat conversations are not organized in the Memory tab.\n28\t\n29\t**Expected Behavior**:\n30\t- All chat conversations are saved to Memory system\n31\t- Conversations are categorized by date/topic\n32\t- Memory tab shows organized chat history\n33\t- Users can search and review past conversations\n34\t\n35\t### 4. Pet Knowledge Sharing\n36\t**New Feature**: Pet automatically shares interesting content with user.\n37\t\n38\t**Content Types**:\n39\t- Historical facts\n40\t- Travel destinations\n41\t- Cultural knowledge\n42\t- Current news\n43\t- Educational topics\n44\t\n45\t**Behavior**:\n46\t- Share at regular intervals (e.g., every 2-4 hours)\n47\t- No sharing during night hours (e.g., 10pm - 8am)\n48\t- Max 1 share per hour to avoid spamming\n49\t- Content based on chat history context\n50\t\n51\t## Acceptance Criteria\n52\t\n53\t- [ ] User sends message and receives AI response\n54\t- [ ] Chat history persists when switching tabs\n55\t- [ ] Chat history persists after page reload\n56\t- [ ] All chat messages saved to Memory system\n57\t- [ ] Memory tab shows organized chat history\n58\t- [ ] Pet shares knowledge topics periodically\n59\t- [ ] No sharing during night hours\n60\t- [ ] Max 1 share per hour\n61\t\n62\t## Files to Modify\n63\t\n64\t| File | Change |\n65\t|------|--------|\n66\t| `src/components/Chat.vue` | Fix sendMessage, add history persistence, add sharing timer |\n67\t| `src/store/pet.ts` | Fix chatWithAI to properly handle responses |\n68\t| `src/components/Memory.vue` | Display chat conversations organized by date |\n69\t| `src/api/llm.ts` | Verify LLM API call works correctly |\n70\t| `src/services/sharing.ts` | New service for pet knowledge sharing |\n71\t\n72\t## Technical Approach\n73\t\n74\t1. **Chat Fix**: Verify `chatWithAI` properly handles API response and adds to chat history\n75\t2. **Persistence**: Ensure `addChatMessageImmediately` saves to DB immediately\n76\t3. **Memory Integration**: Create mapping between chat messages and memory records\n77\t4. **Sharing System**: Create periodic job that runs while chat is open\n78\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0042a016-b05e-49d9-b0f9-6604f20a3a02","uuid":"86efb24e-8201-4530-a5ef-7ce5345d3469","timestamp":"2026-04-10T03:36:04.487Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/aixz/data/hxf/bigmodel/ai_code/trellis-worktrees/feature/fix-chat-integrate-memory/.trellis/tasks/04-10-fix-chat-integrate-memory/prd.md","content":"# Feature: Fix Chat Issues and Integrate Memory System\n\n## Overview\n\nFix critical chat issues and integrate with the Memory system to provide a complete chat experience with persistent history and knowledge sharing.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### 1. Chat Message Delivery Fix\n**Current Issue**: When user sends a message in chat, there is no AI response.\n\n**Expected Behavior**:\n- User message is sent to LLM API\n- AI response is received and displayed\n- No blocking or hanging on send\n\n### 2. Chat History Persistence\n**Current Issue**: When switching tabs and returning to chat, the conversation history is lost.\n\n**Expected Behavior**:\n- Chat history is saved to IndexedDB/Database\n- History persists across tab switches\n- History persists across page reloads\n- Load from DB when chat component mounts\n\n### 3. Memory System Integration\n**Current Issue**: Chat conversations are not organized in the Memory tab.\n\n**Expected Behavior**:\n- All chat conversations are saved to Memory system\n- Conversations are categorized by date/topic\n- Memory tab shows organized chat history\n- Users can search and review past conversations\n\n### 4. Pet Knowledge Sharing\n**New Feature**: Pet automatically shares interesting content with user.\n\n**Content Types**:\n- Historical facts\n- Travel destinations\n- Cultural knowledge\n- Current news\n- Educational topics\n\n**Behavior**:\n- Share at regular intervals (e.g., every 2-4 hours)\n- No sharing during night hours (e.g., 10pm - 8am)\n- Max 1 share per hour to avoid spamming\n- Content based on chat history context\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] User sends message and receives AI response\n- [ ] Chat history persists when switching tabs\n- [ ] Chat history persists after page reload\n- [ ] All chat messages saved to Memory system\n- [ ] Memory tab shows organized chat history\n- [ ] Pet shares knowledge topics periodically\n- [ ] No sharing during night hours\n- [ ] Max 1 share per hour\n\n## Files to Modify\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `src/components/Chat.vue` | Fix sendMessage, add history persistence, add sharing timer |\n| `src/store/pet.ts` | Fix chatWithAI to properly handle responses |\n| `src/components/Memory.vue` | Display chat conversations organized by date |\n| `src/api/llm.ts` | Verify LLM API call works correctly |\n| `src/services/sharing.ts` | New service for pet knowledge sharing |\n\n## Technical Approach\n\n1. **Chat Fix**: Verify `chatWithAI` properly handles API response and adds to chat history\n2. **Persistence**: Ensure `addChatMessageImmediately` saves to DB immediately\n3. **Memory Integration**: Create mapping between chat messages and memory records\n4. **Sharing System**: Create periodic job that runs while chat is open\n","numLines":78,"startLine":1,"totalLines":78}}}
